{{Infobox journal | title = Environmental Science & Technology | editor = David L. Sedlak | discipline = [[Environmental science]], [[environmental engineering]] | abbreviation = Environ. Sci. Technol. | publisher = [[American Chemical Society]] | country = United States | frequency = Biweekly | history = 1967-present | impact = 6.198 | impact-year = 2016 | website = http://pubs.acs.org/journals/esthag/ | cover = est cover.jpg | image_size = 150px | ISSN = 0013-936X | eISSN = 1520-5851 | CODEN = ESTHAG }}
'''''Environmental Science & Technology''''' is a biweekly [[Peer review|peer-reviewed]] [[scientific journal]] published since 1967 by the [[American Chemical Society]]. It covers research in [[environmental science]] and [[environmental technology]], including [[environmental policy]].''Environmental Science & Technology'' has a sister journal, ''[[Environmental Science & Technology Letters]]'', which publishes short communications.
The [[editor-in-chief]] of ''Environmental Science & Technology'' is David L. Sedlak.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://pubs.acs.org/page/esthag/profile.html |title=Editor Profile |publisher=ACS Publications |work=Environmental Science & Technology |accessdate=2017-02-11}}</ref> Previous editors have been: James J. Morgan ([[California Institute of Technology]]; founding editor, 1967-1975), Russell F. Christman ([[University of North Carolina]], 1975-1987), William H. Glaze (University of North Carolina, 1987-2003) and Jerald L. Schnoor (University of Iowa, 2002-2014).
